name: Space Shuttle Orbiter x1
description: A tribute to NASA's iconic Space Shuttle Orbiter on its 40th anniversary of first launch into space.  For as long as I can remember, I've always loved those long lens shots of this shuttle, taken by astronauts/cosmonauts aboard ISS and Mir.   Still to this day probably the most complex thing ever engineered, this is my take on those inspiring photos with the iconic worm logo.  High Res 2496x2496
